<p>If you're not using Doctrine, just make sure to update the user record in the database
however you want.</p>
<h2 id="fetching-the-existing-customer-object">Fetching the Existing Customer Object <a class="headerlink" href="stripe-customers#fetching-the-existing-customer-object" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Now, add the <code>else</code>: this means the user <em>already</em> has a Stripe customer object.
Repeat customer! Instead of creating a new one, just fetch the customer with
<code>\Stripe\Customer::retrieve()</code> and pass it <code>$user-&gt;getStripeCustomerId()</code>:</p>
