<p>Since this user is already in Stripe, we <em>might</em> eventually re-work our checkout
page so that they <em>don't</em> need to re-enter their credit card. But, we haven't done
that yet. And since they just submitted <em>fresh</em> card information, we should <em>update</em>
their account with that. After all, this might be a different card than what they used
the first time they ordered.</p>
<p>To do that, update the <code>source</code> field: set it to <code>$token</code>. To send that update to
Stripe, call <code>$customer-&gt;save()</code>:</p>
